    <string name="debug_ui_redesign_sample_text" translatable="false"><![CDATA[<b>Please review this information carefully:</b><br></br>
<p> Future-dated and recurring payments may be edited or deleted prior to 3:00 PM ET on the Scheduled Payment Date.</p>
<p> Payments may be viewed on your checking account activity screen on the Scheduled Payment Date, typically by 5:00 PM ET or sooner.</p>
<p> Payments may be viewed on your credit card or line of credit account activity screen the business day after your Scheduled Payment Date.</p>
<p> Payments that have been processed are displayed in Recent Transfers within Funds Transfers.</p>
<p> No payment will be processed if the Minimum Payment Due and/or Last Statement Balance on your account is less than or equal to zero ($0) on the Scheduled Payment Date.</p>
<p> If your Last Statement Balance or Other Amount payment is greater than your Current Balance on the Scheduled Payment Date, then a reduced payment amount equal to your Current Balance will be processed.</p>
<p> If your From (funding) account has an insufficient balance on the Scheduled Transfer Date, your payment will not be processed. Please note that if you have established Overdraft Protection from another linked account for your funding account, funds will not be transferred from the Protecting Account to cover your payment and your scheduled payment will not be processed.</p>
<p> If you wish to make changes, please click Back or the back arrow to return to the Schedule a Transfer page. If this information is correct, please click Close to review and submit your transfer.</p>]]> Your payment may be sent electronically or by paper check. Payments that are sent by paper check may
                                            be received and processed by the Payee earlier or later than the date you selected.
                                            If the payment is processed by the Payee earlier than the date you selected, the
                                            amount will be deducted from your account before the date you selected. As a result, we
                                            recommend that you keep sufficient funds in your account to cover your payment
                                            beginning a few business days before the date that you selected and keep such funds
                                            available until the payment is deducted from your account. Please refer to the Online
                                            Banking Online Payments guarantee within the Online Banking Services Agreement for additional information."</string>


